HEADWORD: Nomadic
<hw>No*mad"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/. See
<er>Nomad</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to nomads, or their way of
life; wandering; moving from place to place for subsistence; <as>as, a
<ex>nomadic</ex> tribe</as>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>No*mad"ic*al*ly</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nomadism</ent>⟦br⟧
